      • getTypeCardinality

        public static long getTypeCardinality(Expression symbol,
                                      Registry registry)
        Returns the cardinality of the type of a given variable in the given registry, looking for | Type |, for Type the type of the variable, in the registry global objects. If the size cannot be determined, returns -1. If the size is infinite, returns -2.
        Parameters:
        symbol - a variable
        registry - the registry
        Returns:
        the cardinality of the type of the variable according to the registry or -1 if it cannot be determined.

      • fromTypeExpressionToItsIntrinsicMeaning

        public static Type fromTypeExpressionToItsIntrinsicMeaning(Expression typeExpression,
                                                           Registry registry)
                                                    throws Error
        A method mapping type expressions to their intrinsic Type objects, where "intrinsic" means there is only one possible Type object for them in the registry of grinder (therefore, it cannot be used for, say, categorical types defined by the user and registered in the registry by name only). Current recognized type expressions are Boolean, Integer, and function applications of the type m..n. If there is no such meaning, the method returns null.
        Parameters:
        typeExpression -
        registry - TODO
        Returns:
        Throws:
        Error
